---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Repl from '../../../../components/Repl';
import SchemeRepl from '../../../../components/SchemeRepl';
import Neighbors from "../../../../components/Neighbors.astro";
import PrevNext from "../../../../components/PrevNext.astro";
---

<Layout title="OpenIntro Ch.3 — Probability" favicon="📊">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/statistics/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to statistics</a>

    <h1>Probability</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">OpenIntro Statistics &middot; Ch. 3 &middot; <a href="https://openintro.org/book/operating-systems/">openintro.org/book/os</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>Probability</strong> quantifies uncertainty. The rules are simple: probabilities are between 0 and 1, they add up for disjoint events, and conditional probability lets you update beliefs with new evidence. Bayes' theorem ties it all together.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Basic Rules -->
    <h3>Probability rules</h3>
    <p>For any event A: 0 &le; P(A) &le; 1. For disjoint events: P(A or B) = P(A) + P(B). For non-disjoint events: P(A or B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A and B). The complement rule: P(not A) = 1 - P(A).</p>

    <!-- SVG: Venn diagram -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 360 200" class="w-full max-w-sm" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Sample space rectangle -->
        <rect x="20" y="10" width="320" height="180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3" rx="4"/>
        <text x="35" y="28" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.4">S</text>
        <!-- Circle A -->
        <circle cx="145" cy="100" r="65" fill="#3b82f6" fill-opacity="0.15" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="110" y="105" text-anchor="middle" fill="#3b82f6" font-size="14" fill-opacity="0.7">A</text>
        <!-- Circle B -->
        <circle cx="215" cy="100" r="65" fill="#f59e0b" fill-opacity="0.15" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="250" y="105" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="14" fill-opacity="0.7">B</text>
        <!-- Intersection label -->
        <text x="180" y="105" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="11" fill-opacity="0.6">A&#x2229;B</text>
        <!-- Formula -->
        <text x="180" y="195" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.3">P(A &#x222a; B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A &#x2229; B)</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Probability rules
; P(A or B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A and B)

(define p-a 0.4)    ; P(rain)
(define p-b 0.3)    ; P(traffic)
(define p-ab 0.12)  ; P(rain AND traffic)

; Addition rule (general)
(define p-a-or-b (+ p-a p-b (- p-ab)))
(display "P(rain OR traffic) = ")
(display p-a-or-b) (newline)

; Complement rule
(define p-not-a (- 1 p-a))
(display "P(no rain) = ")
(display p-not-a) (newline)

; If disjoint (mutually exclusive), P(A and B) = 0
(define p-heads 0.5)
(define p-tails 0.5)
(display "P(heads OR tails) = ")
(display (+ p-heads p-tails))
`} />


    <!-- 2. Conditional Probability -->
    <h3>Conditional probability</h3>
    <p>P(A | B) = P(A and B) / P(B). The probability of A, given that B happened. This is how we update probabilities with evidence.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Conditional probability: P(A|B) = P(A and B) / P(B)

(define p-disease 0.01)         ; prevalence
(define p-positive-given-disease 0.95)  ; sensitivity
(define p-positive-given-healthy 0.05)  ; false positive rate

; P(positive) by total probability
(define p-healthy (- 1 p-disease))
(define p-positive
  (+ (* p-positive-given-disease p-disease)
     (* p-positive-given-healthy p-healthy)))

(display "P(positive test) = ")
(display p-positive) (newline)

; P(disease | positive) by Bayes' theorem
(define p-disease-given-positive
  (/ (* p-positive-given-disease p-disease) p-positive))

(display "P(disease | positive) = ")
(display (exact->inexact p-disease-given-positive)) (newline)

; Even with a 95% accurate test, a positive result
; only means ~16% chance of disease when prevalence is 1%
(display "Base rate matters.")
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Bayes' theorem in Python
p_disease = 0.01
p_pos_given_disease = 0.95  # sensitivity
p_pos_given_healthy = 0.05  # false positive rate

p_healthy = 1 - p_disease
p_positive = p_pos_given_disease * p_disease + p_pos_given_healthy * p_healthy

p_disease_given_pos = (p_pos_given_disease * p_disease) / p_positive

print(f"P(positive test) = {p_positive:.4f}")
print(f"P(disease | positive) = {p_disease_given_pos:.4f}")
print(f"Base rate matters.")
`} />
    </div>


    <!-- 3. Independence -->
    <h3>Independence</h3>
    <p>Events A and B are <strong>independent</strong> if P(A | B) = P(A), equivalently P(A and B) = P(A) * P(B). Coin flips are independent. Test results from the same patient are not.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Independence check: P(A and B) =? P(A) * P(B)

; Two coin flips: independent
(define p-h1 0.5)  ; first heads
(define p-h2 0.5)  ; second heads
(define p-both-heads (* p-h1 p-h2))
(display "P(both heads) = ")
(display p-both-heads) (newline)
(display "P(H1) * P(H2) = ")
(display (* p-h1 p-h2)) (newline)
(display "Independent? ")
(display (= p-both-heads (* p-h1 p-h2))) (newline)
(newline)

; Rain and umbrella: NOT independent
(define p-rain 0.3)
(define p-umbrella 0.4)
(define p-rain-and-umbrella 0.25)  ; higher than product
(display "P(rain) * P(umbrella) = ")
(display (* p-rain p-umbrella)) (newline)
(display "P(rain AND umbrella)  = ")
(display p-rain-and-umbrella) (newline)
(display "Independent? ")
(display (= p-rain-and-umbrella (* p-rain p-umbrella)))
`} />


